/-! ## Demo 24 — ELF with an R_BPF_64_64 relocation

Real Anchor / native-Rust binaries link `lddw r1, <addend>` against a
symbol in `.rodata`; the runtime address is unknown at compile time and
the ELF carries a relocation that the loader patches at load time. We
model that here: the `.text` lddw's immediate is zero in the file,
becomes `0x100000000` (the `.rodata` VA) after relocation, and the
program then dereferences that pointer to read the byte `0x42` out of
`.rodata`.

```
  lddw r1, 0           ; placeholder — patched by relocation
  ldxb r0, [r1 + 0]    ; read .rodata[0]
  exit                 ; r0 = 0x42
```

7 sections: null, `.text`, `.rodata`, `.dynsym`, `.dynstr`, `.rel.dyn`,
`.shstrtab`. The `.rel.dyn` entry has type `R_BPF_64_64` (= 1) against
symbol index 1, which lives in `.rodata` at offset 0.
-/

